  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0d9a\u0da7\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0db7\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cricket officials requested permission to attend official functions",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that seven members of the Executive Committee of the Sri Lanka Cricket Institute have requested permission from the Ministry of Sports to participate in the official activities of the ongoing Asia Cup Cricket Tournament and that any trips made or planned to be made by the members of the Executive Committee are for 'official business' purposes related to the development of cricket in Sri Lanka. Sri Lanka Cricket said in a statement that it is nothing but the trips made.",
        "The media reports published on Mr. Arjuna Ranatunga's statement that seven officials of the Sri Lanka Cricket Institute have requested permission to spend crores of rupees to go on a super trip are damaging the image of the Sri Lankan cricket officials who work voluntarily and the officials of the member countries and the Asian Cricket Association during the 2022 Asia Cup cricket tournament. To discuss with, to meet with private sector representatives who can create huge commercial opportunities for Sri Lankan sports, to discuss the future match tour programs in Sri Lanka from 2023 to 2027 and to discuss the renovation work of the Sri Lankan Premier League (LPL) tournament etc. The Sri Lanka Cricket Institute says that many things were to be accomplished.",
        "Although the members of the Sri Lanka Cricket Executive Committee deserve a lot of respect for their honorable service to the game of cricket, the Sri Lanka Cricket Board says that the false statements made by Mr. Arjuna Ranatunga will detract from that respect. The Sri Lanka Cricket Board further emphasizes in the announcement that its operations will be carried out only with the funds earned from the sale of match broadcasting rights."
      ],
